recap_documents.description: Memorandum Opinion and Order: The Court GRANTS IN PART Doe's amended motion for leave to file under seal (Doc.  12 ) and FINDS AS MOOT Doe's original motion (Doc.  7 ). Moreover, the Court ORDERS Doc.  7 -1 to remain under seal but INSTRUC TS the Clerk of Court to unseal the rest of Doc.  7 . Doe has already filed a redacted version of Dan Vencu's declaration,15 so the Court INSTRUCTS the Clerk of Court to unseal Doc. 10 and its attachments. The Court's instructions are the r esult of a page-by-page, line-by-line analysis. Such analysis "is not easy, but it is fundamental" to securing the public's right of access to judicial records. Further, the Court DENIES Doe's motion to proceed under a pseudonym and for entry of a protective order to shield his identity (Doc.  8 ). The protection of maintaining the photo under seal is sufficient to prevent further harm to Doe.  (Ordered by Judge Brantley Starr on 4/1/2025) (ykp)
